INSERT INTO contents VALUES(98,'in golang, how to run a program with source code in different files?',replace('To run a program with source code in different files in Go, you need to first compile the program into an executable file.\n\nAssuming you have multiple source code files located in the same directory, you can use the following command to compile the program:\n\n```shell\ngo build -o myprogram main.go file1.go file2.go\n```\n\nHere, `myprogram` is the name of the executable file you want to create, `main.go`, `file1.go`, and `file2.go` are the names of your source code files.\n\nOnce the program is compiled, you can run it with the following command:\n\n```shell\n./myprogram\n```\n\nAlternatively, you can combine the build and run commands into a single step using the `go run` command:\n\n```shell\ngo run main.go file1.go file2.go\n```\n\nThis will compile and run the program in one step without creating an executable file.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(99,'in golang, how to separate logic to different files for Gin-Gonic framework projects?',replace('To separate logic to different files in a Gin-Gonic framework project in Golang, you can simply create different packages and files for different parts of the logic.\n\n1. Define each package in a separate file: For example, a package for database operations can be defined in a file named `dbops.go`, while a package for user authentication can be defined in a file named `auth.go.`\n\n2. Import all required packages: Import all the packages required in the main file of your Gin-Gonic project. For example, if you have defined a package for database operations, import the package into your main `main.go` file.\n\n3. Use the imported package in your logic: Now you can use the imported packages in your Gin-Gonic project. For instance, to handle a request related to user authentication, you can use the package `auth.go` that you have defined.\n\nBy separating the logic into different packages and files, you can make your Gin-Gonic project more organized and maintainable.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
