INSERT INTO contents VALUES(109,'I want you to act as a Wikipedia page. I will give you the name of a topic, and you will provide a summary of that topic in the format of a Wikipedia page. Your summary should be informative and factual, covering the most important aspects of the topic. Start your summary with an introductory paragraph that gives an overview of the topic. My first topic is “The Great Fire Wall.”',replace('The Great Firewall is a term used to describe China''s system of internet censorship and surveillance. The government uses a variety of technological and legal measures to control what content is accessible to Chinese citizens online. The system is known to block foreign social media websites, news outlets, and search engines, as well as censoring sensitive political content and preventing online activism.\n\nThe Great Firewall operates by monitoring internet traffic and blocking specific keywords, phrases, IP addresses, and domain names. It also employs "human censors" who monitor social media and other online platforms, deleting or blocking content that is deemed inappropriate or politically sensitive. In addition, the government requires websites to register with the government and obtain a permit to operate within China. This permits allows government to supervise and censor their content.\n\nThe Great Firewall has faced criticism both domestically and internationally for impeding freedom of speech and limiting access to information. Some Chinese citizens use VPNs or other technologies to bypass the system, but the government has also cracked down on these methods, leading to arrests and fines.\n\nDespite criticism, Chinese officials have defended the Great Firewall as a necessary measure for national security and protecting citizens from harmful online content. The system is constantly evolving and updating to keep up with changing technologies and methods of online communication.\n\nIn summary, the Great Firewall is China''s system of internet censorship and surveillance. It blocks access to foreign social media websites, news outlets, and search engines, as well as censoring sensitive political content and preventing online activism. The system uses technological and legal measures to control online content, and has faced criticism for impeding freedom of speech and limiting access to information.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(110,'I want you to act as a Wikipedia page. I will give you the name of a topic, and you will provide a summary of that topic in the format of a Wikipedia page. Your summary should be informative and factual, covering the most important aspects of the topic. Start your summary with an introductory paragraph that gives an overview of the topic. My first topic is “清朝”',replace('清朝 (Qing dynasty) was the last imperial dynasty of China, ruling from 1644 to 1912. The dynasty was founded by the Manchu people, who conquered the Ming dynasty and established their own rule over China. In its early years, the Qing dynasty faced significant military, economic, and sociopolitical challenges. However, it eventually developed into a successful and prosperous era, marked by significant cultural and technological advancements.\n\nThe reign of the Qing dynasty was characterized by a strong emphasis on traditional Chinese culture, with a particular focus on Confucian values and classical literature. The dynasty was also noteworthy for its expansion of Chinese territory, conquering and incorporating Tibet, Xinjiang, and Mongolia into the empire. In addition, the Qing dynasty was instrumental in the development of international trade, establishing diplomatic relations with Europe and other parts of Asia.\n\nDespite its many achievements, the Qing dynasty was not without its flaws. It faced significant internal instability, marked by peasant uprisings, political corruption, and elite struggles for power. The dynasty also faced challenges from foreign imperial powers, particularly during the Opium Wars.\n\nIn 1912, the Qing dynasty was overthrown by a republican revolution led by Sun Yat-sen and the Kuomintang. The end of the dynasty marked a significant turning point in Chinese history, ultimately leading to the establishment of the People''s Republic of China. Today, the Qing dynasty is remembered as a significant era in Chinese history, characterized by both progress and challenges as China underwent a period of significant transformation.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(111,'我希望您充当Wikipedia页面。 我会给您一个主题的名称，您将以Wikipedia页面的格式提供该主题的摘要。 您的摘要应该是有益的和事实的，涵盖了该主题的最重要方面。 从介绍性段落开始概述该主题的概述。 我的第一个主题是“中国历史”',replace('中国历史是指自古至今中国境内和中国民族所形成的社会历史。中国历史可以追溯到公元前1600年左右的商朝时期。历经漫长的时间，中国历史留下了大量的文化、哲学、艺术和科学成就，成为世界上最悠久和最繁荣的文明之一。\n\n中国历史中的几个显著时期包括春秋战国时期，秦朝，汉朝，三国时期，唐朝，宋朝，元朝，明朝和清朝。这些时期的政治、社会和文化变迁，对中国的未来产生了深远的影响。在这些时期中，中国历史涌现出了许多著名的皇帝和文化名人，例如秦始皇、汉武帝、李世民、韩愈、苏轼和李清照等。\n\n中国历史经历了许多重要事件，其中最著名的之一是文化大革命。这场运动始于1966年，由毛泽东主导，旨在重塑中国社会。然而，这场运动造成了巨大的社会破坏和暴力行为，直到1976年才结束。\n\n今天，中国已成为世界上最为发达的国家之一，并在经济、科技和文化方面实现了巨大的进步。然而，中国历史依然是研究者和学者们深入探究的领域，因为它为我们提供了重要的历史和文化的遗产。','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(112,'我希望您充当Wikipedia页面。 我会给您一个主题的名称，您将以Wikipedia页面的格式提供该主题的摘要。 您的摘要应该是有益的和事实的，涵盖了该主题的最重要方面。 从介绍性段落开始概述该主题的概述。 我的第一个主题是“秦朝”',replace('秦朝是中国历史上的一个重要朝代，其历史时间跨越了公元前221年至公元前206年，为中华历史上第一个统一的大一统王朝，也是儒家思想的兴起与推动的重要历史时期。\n\n秦朝的创建者为秦始皇，他通过不断的战争和征服使中国大陆的各个国家和民族相互融合，不断扩大和加强自己的势力。他进行了大规模的改革，包括采用标准化的货币、度量衡和文字，修建了许多道路和运河，大幅度提高了中国的交通和通讯水平。同时，秦始皇也进行了许多残酷的政治手段，例如大规模的焚书坑儒，加强中央集权的行政管理，抑制地方权力等举措，使得秦朝在政治上大行其道的同时，也带来了很多人民的不满和反抗。\n\n秦朝除此之外还有很多值得关注的重要历史事件，例如兵马俑的发掘，郑国渠的修建等等，这些事件随着时间的推移，逐渐被人们所认知和传承。\n\n今天，秦朝在中国历史上占据着极其重要的地位，被誉为中国历史的一个重要里程碑，同时也启示着人们对于政治更迭、文化融合的深刻思考。','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(113,'how to export a sqlite3 database and restore it in another server?',replace('To export a SQLite3 database follow these steps:\n\n1. Open a terminal window (command prompt in Windows).\n2. Navigate to the directory where your SQLite3 database is located. \n3. Type the following command to export the database to a SQL file:\n```sh\nsqlite3 mydatabase.db .dump > mydatabase.sql\n```\nMake sure to replace "mydatabase" with the name of your database.\n\n4. Copy the mydatabase.sql file to the new server where you want to restore the database.\n\n\nTo restore the database in the new server follow these steps:\n\n1. Open a terminal window.\n2. Navigate to the directory where you want to create the new SQLite3 database.\n3. Create an empty database using the following command:\n```sh\nsqlite3 newdatabase.db\n```\n\n4. Import the data from the SQL file using the following command:\n```sh\nsqlite3 newdatabase.db < mydatabase.sql\n```\n\nThe newdatabase.db file should now contain the same data as the original mydatabase.db file.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(115,'In sqlite3, I have two databases with the same table structure, how to dump the contents table from the first database chat.db to another database data.db? ',replace('You can use the `.dump` command in SQLite3 to dump the contents of the table from the first database into a SQL script. Then you can run the script on the second database to insert the data.\n\nTo do this:\n\n1. Open the first database in SQLite3\n\n```\nsqlite3 chat.db\n```\n\n2. Dump the contents of the table to a SQL script\n\n```\n.dump table_name > table_name.sql\n```\n\nReplace `table_name` with the actual name of the table you want to dump. This will create a SQL script named `table_name.sql` that contains the table''s schema and data.\n\n3. Open the second database in SQLite3\n\n```\nsqlite3 data.db\n```\n\n4. Run the SQL script on the second database\n\n```\n.read table_name.sql\n```\n\nThis will insert the data from the first database''s table into the equivalent table in the second database. Make sure the table structure is the same between the two databases, otherwise you may get errors.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(116,'In sqlite3, how to dump only the data structure of a table without dump the data in the table?',replace('To dump only the data structure of a table without dumping the data in the table in SQLite3, you can use the ".schema" command followed by the name of the table you want to dump. This will display the SQL statements used to create the table structure, without including any data. Here''s an example:\n\n```\nsqlite> .schema mytable\nCREATE TABLE mytable (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT,\n  age INTEGER\n);\n``` \n\nThis will display the CREATE TABLE statement for the "mytable" table, which includes the column names and data types, as well as any constraints or indexes defined on the table.','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(117,'In sqlite3, how to select the last record from a table?',replace('In order to select the last record from a SQLite database table, you can use the following command:\n\n```\nSELECT * FROM table_name ORDER BY rowid DESC LIMIT 1;\n```\n\nHere, `table_name` is the name of the table you want to select the last record from. The `ORDER BY` clause orders the records in descending order based on their rowid, and `LIMIT 1` limits the output to only the first record (the record with the highest rowid).','\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(118,replace(replace('Question from User:\r\nIn sqlite3, I have two databases with the same table structure, how to dump the contents table from the first database chat.db to another database data.db? \r\nAnswer from AI:\r\nYou can use the `.dump` command in SQLite3 to dump the contents of the table from the first database into a SQL script. Then you can run the script on the second database to insert the data.\r\n\r\nTo do this:\r\n\r\n1. Open the first database in SQLite3\r\n\r\n```\r\nsqlite3 chat.db\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Dump the contents of the table to a SQL script\r\n\r\n```\r\n.dump table_name > table_name.sql\r\n```\r\n\r\nReplace `table_name` with the actual name of the table you want to dump. This will create a SQL script named `table_name.sql` that contains the table''s schema and data.\r\n\r\n3. Open the second database in SQLite3\r\n\r\n```\r\nsqlite3 data.db\r\n```\r\n\r\n4. Run the SQL script on the second database\r\n\r\n```\r\n.read table_name.sql\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will insert the data from the first database''s table into the equivalent table in the second database. Make sure the table structure is the same between the two databases, otherwise you may get errors.\r\n\r\nIn your previous answer, when I run .dump contents after open the database, it gives:\r\n\r\nUsage: .dump ?--preserve-rowids? ?--newlines? ?LIKE-PATTERN?\r\n\r\nFix it.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('To dump the `contents` table from the `chat.db` database using the `.dump` command with default settings, you should first open the database in SQLite3 using the following command:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsqlite3 chat.db\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen, you need to enter the `.dump` command followed by the name of the table you want to dump, like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n.dump contents\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should generate a SQL script with the contents of the `contents` table, that you can save to a file for later use.\r\n\r\nIf you want to specify options for the `.dump` command, you can use the following syntax:\r\n\r\n```\r\n.dump --preserve-rowids --newlines contents > contents.sql\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will dump the `contents` table to a SQL script, with `--preserve-rowids` and `--newlines` options, and save it to a file named `contents.sql`.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(119,replace(replace('Explain the following command in sqlite3:\r\n\r\n.dump --preserve-rowids --newlines contents > contents.sql\r\n\r\nwhat if I don''t want to preserve row id?','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('The `dump` command in SQLite3 is used to write in a script all the SQL commands needed to recreate a database or a table or any other object in it. \r\n\r\nThe following command explained:\r\n\r\n- `.dump`  : It creates a text file with all the SQL commands needed to recreate the database in its current state.\r\n- `--preserve-rowids` : This option instructs SQLite3 to preserve the original row IDs when dumping the data in the designated table. \r\n- `--newlines` : This option introduces newlines to make the output more readable.\r\n- `contents` : It specifies the table whose data is being dumped.\r\n- `> contents.sql` : It saves the dump output to the `contents.sql` file instead of displaying it on the console.\r\n\r\nIf you do not want to preserve the row ids, you may exclude the `--preserve-rowids` option from the command. Thus, the command will become:\r\n\r\n.dump --newlines contents > contents.sql \r\n\r\nThis will create a dump file of the table `contents` without preserving its original row IDs.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(120,replace(replace('Explain the following command in sqlite3:\r\n\r\n.dump --preserve-rowids --newlines contents > contents.sql\r\n\r\nwhat if I don''t want to preserve row id?The `dump` command in SQLite3 is used to write in a script all the SQL commands needed to recreate a database or a table or any other object in it. \r\n\r\nThe following command explained:\r\n\r\n- `.dump`  : It creates a text file with all the SQL commands needed to recreate the database in its current state.\r\n- `--preserve-rowids` : This option instructs SQLite3 to preserve the original row IDs when dumping the data in the designated table. \r\n- `--newlines` : This option introduces newlines to make the output more readable.\r\n- `contents` : It specifies the table whose data is being dumped.\r\n- `> contents.sql` : It saves the dump output to the `contents.sql` file instead of displaying it on the console.\r\n\r\nIf you do not want to preserve the row ids, you may exclude the `--preserve-rowids` option from the command. Thus, the command will become:\r\n\r\n.dump --newlines contents > contents.sql \r\n\r\nThis will create a dump file of the table `contents` without preserving its original row IDs.sqlite> .dump --newlines contents > contents.sql \r\ngives the error:\r\nUsage: .dump ?--preserve-rowids? ?--newlines? ?LIKE-PATTERN?\r\n\r\nfix it:','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('This error occurs when you try to execute the `.dump` command without specifying the name of the table you want to dump. To fix this error, you need to specify the name of the table whose data you want to dump. Here''s an example:\r\n\r\nLet''s assume that you have a table named `employees` in your database. To dump its contents to a file named `employees.sql` without preserving row IDs, you can use the following command:\r\n\r\n```.dump --newlines employees > employees.sql```\r\n\r\nMake sure that you replace `employees` with the name of the table you want to dump.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(121,replace(replace('Fix the following command:\r\nsqlite3 data.db .dump contents > content.sql\r\nError: near "contents": syntax error','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),'sqlite3 data.db ".dump contents" > content.sql',3,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(125,replace(replace('Write the following page with vue framework:\r\n\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n        <meta charset="utf-8" />\r\n        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />\r\n        <title>Users</title>\r\n    </head>\r\n	<style>\r\n	  * {\r\n		text-align: center;\r\n	  }\r\n	  table {\r\n		  margin: 0 auto;\r\n	  }\r\n	</style>\r\n    <body>\r\n        <h1>Users</h1>\r\n		\r\n		<table>\r\n			<tr><th>ID</th><th>Username</th><th>Operation</th></tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>1</td>\r\n                <td>alice</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=1">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>2</td>\r\n                <td>bob</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=2">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>3</td>\r\n                <td>alan</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=3">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>6</td>\r\n                <td>test</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=6">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n		</table>\r\n		\r\n        \r\n            \r\n            \r\n                <h2> Add a new user </h2>\r\n                <form action="/useradd" method="post">\r\n                    <label for="username">Username:</label>\r\n                    <input type="text" id="username" name="username"><br>\r\n                    <label for="password">Password:</label>\r\n                    <input type="password" id="password" name="password"><br>\r\n                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">\r\n                </form>\r\n            \r\n        \r\n    </body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace('<template>\n  <div>\n    <h1>Users</h1>\n    <table>\n      <tr>\n        <th>ID</th>\n        <th>Username</th>\n        <th>Operation</th>\n      </tr>\n      <tr v-for="user in users" :key="user.id">\n        <td>{{ user.id }}</td>\n        <td>{{ user.username }}</td>\n        <td><a @click="deleteUser(user.id)">delete</a></td>\n      </tr>\n    </table>\n\n    <h2> Add a new user </h2>\n    <form @submit.prevent="addUser">\n      <label for="username">Username:</label>\n      <input type="text" id="username" v-model="newUser.username"><br>\n      <label for="password">Password:</label>\n      <input type="password" id="password" v-model="newUser.password"><br>\n      <input type="submit" value="Submit">\n    </form>\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  data() {\n    return {\n      users: [\n        { id: 1, username: "alice" },\n        { id: 2, username: "bob" },\n        { id: 3, username: "alan" },\n        { id: 6, username: "test" },\n      ],\n      newUser: { username: "", password: "" },\n    };\n  },\n  methods: {\n    addUser() {\n      // send post request to server to add new user\n      // after success, update users array with new user and reset newUser object\n      this.users.push({\n        id: this.users.length + 1,\n        username: this.newUser.username,\n      });\n      this.newUser = { username: "", password: "" };\n    },\n    deleteUser(id) {\n      // send delete request to server to delete user with id\n      // after success, remove user from users array\n      this.users = this.users.filter((user) => user.id !== id);\n    },\n  },\n};\n</script>\n\n<style scoped>\n* {\n  text-align: center;\n}\ntable {\n  margin: 0 auto;\n}\n</style>','\n',char(10)),1,1);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(126,'how to mv home directory to another disk in linux',replace('To move the home directory to another disk in Linux, follow these steps:\n\n1. Create a new directory on the target disk where you want to move the home directory, such as /mnt/newhome.\n\n2. Log in as root or use sudo to elevate privileges.\n\n3. Use rsync or cp to copy the contents of the current home directory to the new directory on the target disk. For example:\n\n   `rsync -avz /home/ /mnt/newhome`\n\n   or \n\n   `cp -r /home/* /mnt/newhome`\n\n   Note: the -a option of rsync preserves all file attributes, including permissions, while the -r option of cp copies all files recursively.\n\n4. Verify that the files have been copied correctly by comparing the source and target directories.\n\n5. Edit the /etc/passwd file to update the home directory for all users. For example:\n\n   `user:x:1000:1000:User Name:/mnt/newhome/user:/bin/bash`\n\n   or \n\n   `sed -i ''s/\/home\//\/mnt\/newhome\//g'' /etc/passwd`\n\n   This changes the home directory for the user from /home/user to /mnt/newhome/user.\n\n6. Reboot the system or use the chown command to change the ownership of the new home directory to the appropriate user. For example, to change the ownership of the new directory for the user "user":\n\n   `chown -R user:user /mnt/newhome/user`\n\n   Note: -R option of chown changes the ownership recursively.\n\n7. Test the new home directory by logging in as a user and verifying that all files and settings are accessible.\n\n8. If everything is working correctly, you can delete the old home directory using rm or mv command. For example:\n\n   `rm -rf /home` \n\n   or \n\n   `mv /home /home.old`','\n',char(10)),1,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(127,'Write a function in golang that calculates fibonacci',replace('numbers up to a given limit:\n\n```\npackage main\n\nimport "fmt"\n\nfunc fibonacci(max int) []int {\n    if max < 0 {\n        return []int{}\n    }\n\n    result := []int{0}\n    if max == 0 {\n        return result\n    }\n\n    a, b := 0, 1\n    for b <= max {\n        result = append(result, b)\n        a, b = b, a+b\n    }\n\n    return result\n}\n\nfunc main() {\n    fmt.Println(fibonacci(0))  // [0]\n    fmt.Println(fibonacci(1))  // [0 1]\n    fmt.Println(fibonacci(2))  // [0 1 1 2]\n    fmt.Println(fibonacci(20)) // [0 1 1 2 3 5 8 13]\n}\n```','\n',char(10)),1,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(128,'Write a function in golang that calculates the nth fibonacci number',replace('Here is an example function in Golang that calculates the nth Fibonacci number:\n\n```go\nfunc fibonacci(n int) int {\n    if n == 0 || n == 1 {\n        return n\n    } else {\n        return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe function takes an integer `n` as input, which represents the index of the Fibonacci number to calculate. It uses recursion to calculate the Fibonacci number by adding the two previous numbers in the sequence (starting with 0 and 1).\n\nFor example, calling `fibonacci(5)` would return the 5th Fibonacci number, which is 5.','\n',char(10)),1,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(129,'Write a function in golang that calculates the nth fibonacci number, don''t use recursion algorithm',replace('```\nfunc fib(n int) int {\n  if n <= 1 {\n    return n\n  }\n  \n  a, b := 0, 1\n  for i := 2; i <= n; i++ {\n    c := a + b\n    a = b\n    b = c\n  }\n  return b\n}\n```\n\nThis function uses a loop to calculate the nth fibonacci number. It also includes a base case for the first two fibonacci numbers.','\n',char(10)),1,0);
INSERT INTO contents VALUES(130,replace(replace('Add a navigator bar to the following html with one button to homepage, the other button to logout\r\n\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n        <meta charset="utf-8" />\r\n        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />\r\n        <title>Users</title>\r\n    </head>\r\n	<style>\r\n	  * {\r\n		text-align: center;\r\n	  }\r\n	  table {\r\n		  margin: 0 auto;\r\n	  }\r\n	</style>\r\n    <body>\r\n        <h1>Users</h1>\r\n		\r\n		<table>\r\n			<tr><th>ID</th><th>Username</th><th>Operation</th></tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>1</td>\r\n                <td>alice</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=1">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>2</td>\r\n                <td>bob</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=2">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>3</td>\r\n                <td>alan</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=3">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n                <tr>\r\n                <td>9</td>\r\n                <td>test</td>\r\n                <td><a href="/userdel?id=9">delete</a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n            \r\n		</table>\r\n\r\n                <h2> Add a new user </h2>\r\n                <form action="/useradd" method="post">\r\n                    <label for="username">Username:</label>\r\n                    <input type="text" id="username" name="username"><br>\r\n                    <label for="password">Password:</label>\r\n                    <input type="password" id="password" name="password"><br>\r\n                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">\r\n                </form>\r\n           \r\n    </body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace('<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n    <head>\n     